oups/382445/items/F66S4X3M\">https://www.zotero.org/groups/382445/items/F66S4X3M\u003C/a>\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"edition-interpretive\" lang=\"grc\">  \u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-interpretive\">  \u003Ca id=\"al1-interpretive\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]ΜΑΛ[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]ΔΡΥΜΑ \u003C/span>\u003C/div>  \u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Valentina Mignosa; edition source: \u003Ca href=\"https://www.zotero.org/groups/382445/items/F66S4X3M\">https://www.zotero.org/groups/382445/items/F66S4X3M\u003C/a>\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"edition-diplomatic\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-diplomatic\">\u003Ca id=\"al1-diplomatic\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]ΜΑΛ[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]ΔΡΥΜΑ\u003C/span>\u003C/div>\u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>\u003C/div>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"facsimile-images\">\u003Ch2>Facsimile Images\u003C/h2>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"apparatus\">\u003Ch4>Apparatus criticus\u003C/h4>\u003Cp>  \u003C/p>\u003Cp>Text of IGPalermo\u003C/p>  \u003Cp>\u003C/p>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"translation\">\u003Ch2> translation\u003C/h2>\u003Cp class=\"translation-author\">  \u003C/p>\u003Cp>  \u003C/p>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"commentary\">\u003Ch2>commentary\u003C/h2>  \u003Cp>The text is very difficult to read and the interpretation much disputed, although Garbini was confident that it is not Punic. Guarducci and Garbini debated the presence of various letter forms, whether Megaran or from Selinunte, and Guarducci speculated that it was a non-Greek inscription in Greek letters. It seems most likely to be a damaged and difficult to read funerary inscription.\u003C/p>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"bibliography\">\u003Ch2>bibliography\u003C/h2>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli> Gabrici NSA 1917 344 no.4 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001392\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001392\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003Cli> Manni Piraino 1963 152 n.33 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001781\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001781\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003Cli> Garbini 1964-1965 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001968\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001968\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003Cli> Guarducci 1964-1965 487 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001927\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001927\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003Cli> Manni Piraino 1973 104 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000531\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000531\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"handnote\">\u003Cp>There is some debate over the letter forms, due to the poor state of the stone, and whether various epichoric letters are present.\u003C/p> Line 1  30-45  Interlineation line 1 to 2    \u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"license\"> Licensed under a Creative Commons-Attribution 4.0 licence. \u003C/div>",[243,246,249,252,255,258,261,264],{"id":244,"html":245},"editions","\u003Cdiv class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Valentina Mignosa; edition source: \u003Ca href=\"https://www.zotero.org/groups/382445/items/F66S4X3M\">https://www.zotero.org/groups/382445/items/F66S4X3M\u003C/a>\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"edition-interpretive\" lang=\"grc\">  \u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-interpretive\">  \u003Ca id=\"al1-interpretive\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]ΜΑΛ[\u003Cspan di